definition.value: This is an AE which may be overt or subtle and can occasionally cause life-threatening emergencies at birth.
This is an AE which is an inflammatory condition of the lung primarily at birth affecting the small air sacs known as alveoli .
This is an AE which represent a diverse group of abnormalities, ranging from asymptomatic incidental findings to causes of sudden cardiac death.
This is an AE which is a condition of increased blood pressure within the arteries of the lungs at birth.

This is an AE which is often the result of congenital malformations and is observed in isolation or as part of a larger pathologic process, as in Tetralogy of Fallot, Noonan syndrome, and congenital rubella syndrome.

This is an AE which is a condition present at birth regardless of its cause which occured on renal.
This is an AE which  can occur in a developing fetus of a pregnant woman who has contracted rubella, usually in the first trimester.
This is an AE which is syphilis present in utero and at birth, and occurs when a child is born to a mother with syphilis.
This is an AE which is a neoplasm containing tissues foreign to the site of origin or containing more than one embryonic germ cell layer.
This is an AE which can occurs spontaneous and excessive bleeding.
This is an AE which is a genetically and clinically heterogeneous group of platelet disorders that are characterized by thrombocytopenia since birth.
This is an AE which is a rare occurrence and associates with cleft palate may be considered as evidence of close interrelation of embryogenesis of the tongue and palate.
This is an AE which is defined as a contracture or fibrosis of the Sternocleidomastoid muscle, on one side, leading to a homolateral inclination and contralateral rotation of the face and chin.

This is an AE which is a type of congenital valvular heart disease in which the tricuspid valve of the heart, located between the right atrium and right ventricle, does not close completely when the right ventricle contracts (systole).
This is an AE which is a health condition where the abdominal wall behind the navel is congenital damaged.
This is an AE which might be associated with a detrimental effect on the probability of pregnancy achievement, spontaneous abortion and on the obstetric outcome of each pregnancy.
This is an AE which is a congenital condition in which urine flows retrograde, or backward, from the bladder into one or both ureters and then to the renal calyx or kidneys.
This is an AE which is a defect in the structure of the heart or great vessels that is present at birth.

This is an AE which is small dilated blood vessels that can occur near the surface of the skin or mucous membranes, measuring between 0.5 and 1 millimeter in diameter and is  congenital.

This is an AE which is often associated with abnormal PA hemodynamics including increased pressure drop (Δp) and reduced asymmetric flow (Q), which may result in right ventricular dysfunction.
This is an AE which is a congenital heart valve disorder. Blood going from the heart to the lungs goes through the pulmonary valve, whose purpose is to prevent blood from flowing back to the heart.
This is an AE which is the arrangement of digits (fingers and toes) on the hands, feet, or sometimes wings of a tetrapod animal.

This is an AE which is a congenital oral anomaly that may decrease the mobility of the tongue tip and is caused by an unusually short, thick lingual frenulum, a membrane connecting the underside of the tongue to the floor of the mouth.
This is an AE which is a rare disorder characterized by congenital absence of skin.
This is an AE which  refers to a lens opacity which is present at birth.
This is an AE which may occur both as a unilateral and as a bilateral form with a family disposition for dacryostenosis.
This is an AE which is an abnormal difference in body structure.
This is an AE which is a group of non-communicableepilepsy congenital disorders characterized by recurrent epileptic seizures.
This is an AE which is an abnormal difference in body structure and it can be related to a congenital disorder, genetic syndrome or birth defect.

This is an AE which is the heart block that is diagnosed in fetus (in utero) or within the first 28 days after birth (neonatal period), some studies also include the diagnosis during early childhood to the definition of CHB.
This is an AE which is the congenital abnormal exit of tissue or an organ, such as the bowel, through the wall of the cavity in which it normally resides.
This is an AE which may refer to an eye diseases :Vitelliform macular dystrophy, an irregular autosomal dominant eye disorder.
This is an AE which as a pilonidal variety that is of no neurosurgical significance and a deep version with extension to the central nervous system.
This is an AE which the hair loss typically presents itself as either a receding front hairline, loss of hair on the crown (vertex) of the scalp, or a combination of both.
This is an AE which is a disorder that results in recurrent attacks of severe swelling.

This is an AE which is a genetic disorder characterized by excessive intestinal absorption of dietary iron, resulting in a pathological increase in total body iron stores.
This is an AE which is an abnormality of red blood cells, or erythrocytes and is a chronic disease with no cure.
This is an AE which  is a set of rare brain disorders where the whole or parts of the surface of the brain appear smooth.

This is an AE which is a disorder of pregnancy characterized by the onset of high blood pressure and often a significant amount of protein in the urine.
This is an AE which is a genetic disorder that results in the destruction of nerve cells in the brain and spinal cord.
This is an AE which is a severe, complex malformation of monozygotic twinning.
This is an AE which is the slowness of thought common to many disorders of the brain.
